    <title ixia_locid="107">Changing the MTU for a Data Interface Using the CLI</title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="108"><draft-comment author="jmaran" ixia_locid="111">May want to remove the Web
            administration reference as this is the CLI topic (add xref in
        body?)???</draft-comment>You can change the MTU value for a data interface from the Web
        administration interface or the CLI.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="109">Edward Knowlton</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N10029_N10026_N10001" ixia_locid="52">
            <p ixia_locid="105"><draft-comment author="jmaran" ixia_locid="112">The way this topic relates to its
                    sibling topic for doing the same process with the Web interface is inconsistent
                    with how it is handled for the other "Changing" topics in the "System
                    Configuration Management" topic map (lav1466012726255). The other topics seem to
                    have the CLI subordinate to the Web interface topic rather than parallel. I
                    actually thing they are better parallel but the titles should be updated to be
                    "Changing the MTU for a Data Interface Using the Web Interface" vs. just
                    "Changing the MTU for a Data Interface".</draft-comment><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="106">CGTS-1306 procedure updated</draft-comment>The
                MTU must be changed while all the compute hosts attached to the provider network are
                locked.</p>
            <p ixia_locid="53">You can use CLI commands to lock and unlock hosts, and to modify the
                MTU on the hosts.</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="80"><systemoutput ixia_locid="55">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="56">system host-lock <varname ixia_locid="57">nodeName</varname></userinput>
<systemoutput ixia_locid="81">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="82">system host-if-modify <varname ixia_locid="29">nodeName</varname> <varname ixia_locid="83">ifname</varname> --imtu <varname ixia_locid="30">mtu_size</varname></userinput>
<systemoutput ixia_locid="60">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="61">system host-unlock <varname ixia_locid="62">nodeName</varname></userinput></codeblock>
            <p ixia_locid="84">Where:</p>
            <parml>
                <plentry ixia_locid="85">
                    <pt ixia_locid="86"><varname ixia_locid="87">nodename</varname></pt>
                    <pd ixia_locid="88">
                        <p ixia_locid="89"> is the name of the host</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry ixia_locid="90">
                    <pt ixia_locid="91"><varname ixia_locid="92">ifname</varname></pt>
                    <pd ixia_locid="93">
                        <p ixia_locid="94"> is the name of the interface</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
                <plentry ixia_locid="95">
                    <pt ixia_locid="96"><varname ixia_locid="97">mtu_size</varname></pt>
                    <pd ixia_locid="98">
                        <p ixia_locid="99"> is the new MTU value</p>
                    </pd>
                </plentry>
            </parml>
            <p ixia_locid="100"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="110">US82332 interface
                    names</draft-comment>For example:</p>
            <codeblock ixia_locid="101"><systemoutput ixia_locid="102">~(keystone_admin)$ </systemoutput><userinput ixia_locid="103">system host-if-modify compute-0 enp0s8 --imtu 1496</userinput>
</codeblock>
            <note id="note_N10067_N10026_N10023_N10001" ixia_locid="63">
                <p ixia_locid="64">You cannot set the MTU on a compute node interface to a value
                    smaller than the largest MTU used on its provider networks.</p>
            </note>
        </context>
    </taskbody>
